You're making fun of me!

23:14.852 --> 23:17.844
YOUNG LETTIE MAE: I ain't making fun!
JOE: Know how hard I work to make you happy?

23:18.022 --> 23:20.889
You gonna put your hands on me?
You gonna put your hands on me?

23:21.067 --> 23:22.932
-You put your hands on me, goddamn it!
-Aah!

23:23.111 --> 23:25.022
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

23:26.489 --> 23:28.571
You gonna put your hands on me....

23:28.783 --> 23:31.525
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

23:34.122 --> 23:35.532
[WHIMPERING]

23:48.803 --> 23:50.714
Fuck this. I am done.

23:52.307 --> 23:54.889
Don't do this. No! Don't do this. No.

23:55.059 --> 23:57.015
-You hear me?
-Baby, look-- No!

23:57.228 --> 24:01.437
-|'m done.
-No, don't do this. Don't do this, Joe, no.

24:01.649 --> 24:03.310
No!

24:03.484 --> 24:05.440
No, don't do this.

24:05.612 --> 24:07.443
[ENGINE STARTS]

24:09.490 --> 24:12.527
No.

24:14.454 --> 24:19.824
How am I gonna do all this without you?

24:20.043 --> 24:21.783
[YOUNG LETTIE MAE SOBBING]

24:49.155 --> 24:51.942
I'm sorry I didn't pull that trigger.

24:52.158 --> 24:54.274
I should've pulled it long before that day.

24:54.452 --> 24:55.942
What?

24:56.579 --> 24:59.116
No, no.

25:00.208 --> 25:01.698
That's not on you.

25:03.086 --> 25:05.077
I was your mama.

25:05.296 --> 25:07.002
You weren't supposed to save me.

25:07.173 --> 25:08.288
You were a good mama.

25:09.175 --> 25:11.166
I wanted to save you, but I couldn't.

25:12.095 --> 25:14.552
And after that day, everything changed.

25:15.723 --> 25:17.588
I'm sorry.

25:17.767 --> 25:19.974
-I was weak.
-No.

25:20.770 --> 25:23.136
Bad stuff happened to you.

25:23.856 --> 25:25.232
That's all.

25:28.486 --> 25:31.478
Bad stuff happened to you too.

25:33.366 --> 25:34.697
I was supposed to do better.

25:34.909 --> 25:38.401
No more blame, Mama.

25:39.664 --> 25:40.995
Forgive yourself.

25:45.253 --> 25:47.539
And let me go.

25:51.968 --> 25:53.504
How?

25:53.678 --> 25:56.135
You go on living.

25:56.347 --> 25:58.633
Promise me?

26:06.607 --> 26:08.393
I promise.

27:00.745 --> 27:03.157
JASON: Here you go, Tonto.
-You sure you're okay?

27:03.331 --> 27:04.912
HOLLY:
Oh, thank God!

27:05.124 --> 27:06.159
I'm so sorry.

27:06.375 --> 27:09.287
I swear I'll never run away
for any reason, Daddy.

27:09.504 --> 27:11.210
-I promise--
-Shh-shh-shh. Y'all need to shut up.

27:11.380 --> 27:16.670
No more promises and no more apologies.
Let's just hug you.

27:18.221 --> 27:20.052
[ANDY SIGHS]

27:23.643 --> 27:26.806
-Sheriff Bellefleur.
ANDY: Hoyt, I heard about what you did.

27:27.021 --> 27:28.852
Thank you, man.

27:29.065 --> 27:30.805
Thank you.

27:32.109 --> 27:33.440
Thank you.

27:54.674 --> 27:56.289
You okay?

27:58.094 --> 27:59.675
Yeah.

28:02.139 --> 28:06.303
Listen, there are no words
to express just how much I....

28:08.646 --> 28:09.681
Thank you.

28:11.440 --> 28:14.853
I'm just glad I got here when I did.

28:18.030 --> 28:19.566
I'm Jessica.

28:19.740 --> 28:21.696
Jessica, it's nice to meet you.

28:21.868 --> 28:23.699
I'm Hoyt.

28:25.079 --> 28:27.035
-Hi, Hoyt.
-Hi.

28:29.000 --> 28:31.082
ANDY:
All right, everybody. Let's get out of here.

28:31.252 --> 28:34.415
Let's go home. Doesn't that sound good?

28:34.589 --> 28:36.580
We all stick together now. That's the key.

28:36.799 --> 28:38.664
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

28:39.468 --> 28:40.969
Hey, are you okay?

28:42.597 --> 28:44.428
I don't know.

28:48.811 --> 28:51.678
JESSICA:
Well, you know, Adilyn, I'm protecting her.

28:55.192 --> 28:58.901
Who is she, the redhead?

29:00.197 --> 29:02.062
That's-- That's Jess.

29:04.452 --> 29:06.534
Is she your girlfriend?

29:10.833 --> 29:15.042
Honestly, I don't know what to call her.

29:17.965 --> 29:19.546
Oh.

29:26.015 --> 29:27.551
[BILL GRUNTING]

29:28.476 --> 29:30.091
No.

29:33.230 --> 29:35.141
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

29:44.200 --> 29:46.942
-Eric!
-Nice robe.

29:53.584 --> 29:55.620
Where are your veins?

29:55.795 --> 29:56.830
Gone.

29:57.046 --> 29:58.252
Are you healed?

29:58.422 --> 30:00.037
Well, I can't tell you how...

30:00.257 --> 30:04.170
...but I came looking for you because
I wanted you to know I'm gonna be okay.

30:06.305 --> 30:07.966
Bill's sick.

30:09.850 --> 30:11.351
What?

30:11.519 --> 30:14.977
Hep-V. He has it.

30:15.147 --> 30:16.432
Fuck.

30:17.733 --> 30:20.224
Is there something
you're not understanding?

30:20.444 --> 30:23.026
If there's a cure, he needs it.

30:23.197 --> 30:24.562
-There is one.
-Where?

30:24.740 --> 30:27.857
-It's not ready yet.
-What do you mean, it's not ready?

30:28.035 --> 30:30.117
Whatever it is, it worked on you.

30:30.329 --> 30:31.569
Give me a minute to think.

30:31.789 --> 30:34.906
No, no. Eric, he's dying.

30:35.126 --> 30:38.789
It's accelerating at a crazy rate
because of my blood.

30:38.963 --> 30:40.248
I gave it to him.

30:45.553 --> 30:48.841
-Dawn is coming.
-I don't give a shit.

30:49.056 --> 30:52.298
Sookie, I'll come back tomorrow night.

30:52.518 --> 30:55.806
-I don't think he even has until tomorrow night.
-Trust me.

30:56.814 --> 30:59.772
Stay here. I'll be back.

31:00.526 --> 31:03.108
Motherfucker.

31:33.934 --> 31:37.347
Well, that went pretty well. Hm?

31:40.399 --> 31:43.436
I gotta stop making bad decisions, Jess.

31:44.570 --> 31:47.437
Speaking of decisions...

31:47.656 --> 31:49.442
...about the other night....

31:50.785 --> 31:52.195
Oh, that's not what I meant.

31:52.411 --> 31:53.947
No, I know-- I know you didn't.

31:54.121 --> 31:57.534
I never thought anything we ever did
was a bad decision.

31:59.210 --> 32:01.201
Except when I betrayed you.

32:02.338 --> 32:04.169
Or shot you.

32:04.381 --> 32:07.714
Or gotten you locked up in a prison camp.

32:08.636 --> 32:10.797
You know what the funny thing is?

32:12.223 --> 32:14.930
I never felt betrayed by you.

32:16.936 --> 32:18.722
Not even when you were being a dick.

32:18.938 --> 32:23.307
-Well, that's good, I guess.
-Yeah.

32:23.526 --> 32:26.814
Unless it's because you never
took me seriously to begin with.

32:26.987 --> 32:28.818
No.

32:28.989 --> 32:31.696
No, Jason, that is not it.

32:31.909 --> 32:33.365
It's just....

32:35.079 --> 32:40.415
You know how our paths
have crisscrossed, and the timing....

32:41.502 --> 32:42.992
I know what you mean.

32:43.212 --> 32:48.127
Seeing you with Hoyt tonight
brought it all back for me.

32:48.300 --> 32:51.167
Just how complicated things are
between us, you know?

32:54.140 --> 32:57.507
-Can I be real honest with you?
-Please.

32:57.726 --> 33:02.846
I actually feel like our relationship
is one of the least complicated in my life.

33:04.400 --> 33:06.106
Really.

33:06.277 --> 33:07.562
When I look back on us...

33:07.778 --> 33:11.236
...I think about all the times
that you were there for me.

33:12.241 --> 33:15.608
When you gave me exactly what I needed...

33:15.786 --> 33:18.163
...at the exact moment that I needed it.

33:18.330 --> 33:21.572
-Kind of like the other night?
-Yeah.

33:21.750 --> 33:23.832
I feel like when we're together...

33:24.003 --> 33:27.416
...we're in a little bubble, you know,
just floating above the ground.

33:27.631 --> 33:29.667
And I know we can't stay there...

33:29.884 --> 33:33.968
...but it makes coming back down to earth
feel better.

33:37.099 --> 33:38.430
What do you call that?

33:39.518 --> 33:42.635
I don't know if there's an official name.

33:43.689 --> 33:46.476
But why don't we think of it as, um...

33:48.235 --> 33:50.317
...like, a beautiful friendship?

33:52.531 --> 33:54.487
Yeah.

33:57.036 --> 33:58.822
I should go and be with Bill.

33:59.705 --> 34:01.787
You should.

34:04.668 --> 34:06.954
Hey, Jess.

34:08.923 --> 34:14.509
I'm here for you, if you need me.

34:50.881 --> 34:52.291
Excuse me?

34:52.508 --> 34:53.543
[MAN 1 SPEAKS IN JAPANESE]

34:53.717 --> 34:55.253
I'm here to see Eric Northman.
I'm a friend.

34:55.469 --> 34:56.925
[SHOUTS IN JAPANESE]

34:57.096 --> 34:59.883
In English? Any of y'all speak English?

35:00.057 --> 35:01.217
I speak English.

35:01.433 --> 35:03.389
Why didn't you say so sooner?

35:03.602 --> 35:05.388
What's your business here?

35:05.562 --> 35:07.974
I'm here to see Eric Northman.

35:09.483 --> 35:11.644
You are a very brave girl.

35:12.695 --> 35:14.777
Brave and stupid.

35:14.989 --> 35:17.355
So I've been told.

35:22.454 --> 35:25.446
PAM:
I hate those bottles. Talk microwavable cans.

35:25.624 --> 35:27.956
GUS:
Not sure if that's possible, Miss De Beaufort.

35:28.168 --> 35:30.375
[SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

35:34.633 --> 35:37.170
MAN 1:
--Sookie Stackhouse. Mr. Northman....

35:41.974 --> 35:45.637
Let's meet this Sookie Stackhouse, Shall we?

35:45.853 --> 35:47.639
[SPEAKS IN JAPAN ESE]

35:47.938 --> 35:50.099
[MAN 1 & MAN 2 SPEAK IN JAPANESE]

35:52.776 --> 35:54.767
[DOOR OPENS]

36:03.454 --> 36:06.617
I don't mean to bother y'all.

36:06.832 --> 36:11.542
I was just hoping for
a minute alone with Eric.

36:11.712 --> 36:14.419
Tell me, how do you two know each other?

36:15.466 --> 36:18.173
She's just another fangbanger.

36:18.385 --> 36:22.754
I fucked her once a couple years ago
and now I can't get rid of her.

36:22.973 --> 36:24.679
She keeps coming back for more.

36:24.892 --> 36:26.928
Well, if that's true...

36:28.562 --> 36:32.225
...what a very lucky man you are.

36:39.948 --> 36:41.529
[SPEAKS IN JAPAN ESE]

36:41.700 --> 36:44.191
-Hey!
-Mr. Gus, you don't wanna do that.

36:44.411 --> 36:47.949
If all this girl is to you
is just another fangbanger...

36:48.123 --> 36:49.624
