36:49.833 --> 36:51.243
I'm not protecting her.

36:51.460 --> 36:55.453
But this particular fangbanger's brother
happens to be with the sheriff's department.

36:55.672 --> 36:59.460
And if she were to go missing,
he'd come looking for her.

36:59.635 --> 37:01.921
He's done that in the past.

37:02.930 --> 37:05.216
Let me take care of this.

37:05.432 --> 37:07.593
I'll glamour her.

37:07.810 --> 37:10.096
That'll leave us less vulnerable.

37:14.066 --> 37:15.146
[SPEAKS IN JAPAN ESE]

37:22.741 --> 37:24.026
Hello, Sookie.

37:25.786 --> 37:26.821
Hello.

37:26.995 --> 37:29.987
I thought I told you not to come here.

37:30.165 --> 37:31.496
I couldn't wait.

37:31.708 --> 37:34.199
It's really beneath you
the way you keep showing up...

37:34.378 --> 37:36.960
...begging for it, understand?

37:37.131 --> 37:39.087
I understand.

37:39.258 --> 37:41.089
I know where you live.

37:41.260 --> 37:42.750
GUS:
I don 't fucking trust these two.

37:42.928 --> 37:45.590
But he wouldn 't fuck me,
not now with what’s downstairs.

37:45.764 --> 37:47.345
But something ain 't fucking right.

37:47.516 --> 37:51.759
You will never come back here. You will
get back in your car and you will drive home.

37:51.979 --> 37:55.142
And should I ever feel inclined to see you...

37:55.315 --> 37:56.521
...I will come to you.

37:57.609 --> 38:00.772
You never saw these men,
you never saw me.

38:00.946 --> 38:02.811
I never saw you.

38:03.031 --> 38:04.896
Excellent.

38:07.119 --> 38:08.780
Off you go.

38:16.503 --> 38:17.583
[ROCK MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

38:17.754 --> 38:19.494
Mm.

38:20.215 --> 38:23.423
Arlene, is something different?

38:23.635 --> 38:25.591
Because these eggs, they taste amazing.

38:25.762 --> 38:28.890
-You do something different to the eggs?
-No, ma'am.

38:30.350 --> 38:33.342
Must be having a taste of the familiar back.

38:33.562 --> 38:34.847
Maybe.

38:35.898 --> 38:37.809
Speaking of familiar. Hey, Hoyt.

38:38.025 --> 38:39.390
Hey, Arlene. Ahem.

38:39.610 --> 38:41.601
ARLENE: Can I get you something?
-Coffee.

38:43.739 --> 38:47.152
-|s it okay?
-Uh, yeah, sure thing.

38:48.452 --> 38:51.114
-Yeah.
-Holler if you need me.

38:57.377 --> 39:00.505
-How you holding up?
-Whoo.

39:01.673 --> 39:03.004
Been better.

39:04.134 --> 39:06.045
I didn't sleep a lick.

39:06.220 --> 39:11.260
Well, it's no wonder, man.
That was one hell of a day yesterday.

39:11.433 --> 39:18.430
The weird thing is I wasn't up all night
thinking about my mom or Brigette...

39:19.066 --> 39:21.352
...which is what I should've been doing.

39:21.527 --> 39:23.939
Well, it ain't no fun thinking about
the hard things.

39:24.154 --> 39:27.863
Which is why I spend
so much time not thinking. Ha, ha!

39:28.075 --> 39:30.782
-Yeah, you heard me. Ha-ha-ha.
-Yeah. Heh, heh.

39:30.953 --> 39:32.534
-Arlene.
ARLENE: Yep?

39:32.746 --> 39:35.488
HOYT: You bring us two Miller Lites?
-Coming up.

39:37.209 --> 39:39.916
-Heh-heh-heh.
-Attaboy.

39:41.755 --> 39:45.623
HOYT:
You know that redhead girl from last night?

39:48.470 --> 39:50.711
-Jessica?
-Yeah.

39:53.934 --> 39:55.515
Yeah.

39:58.939 --> 40:00.600
You two...?

40:05.070 --> 40:08.107
No, Mr. Fortenberry, we are not.

40:08.282 --> 40:11.365
I don't want you to get
the wrong idea about me.

40:12.494 --> 40:13.950
I care for Brigette.

40:14.121 --> 40:15.702
I'm not a fickle guy.

40:15.872 --> 40:17.408
Yeah, I know you ain't.

40:17.583 --> 40:21.667
It's just-- There's just something
about Jessica L...

40:22.504 --> 40:23.835
I can't shake it.

40:26.216 --> 40:28.923
She's going through a hard time right now.

40:29.636 --> 40:32.048
Her, uh, maker...

40:32.222 --> 40:33.883
...he's dying of Hep-V.

40:34.057 --> 40:36.048
Oh, man.

40:37.978 --> 40:39.514
Who is it? Do you mind me asking?

40:39.688 --> 40:41.929
No, it's Bill Compton.

40:42.649 --> 40:44.935
-It's Vampire Bill?
-Yes.

40:45.110 --> 40:46.941
I always liked him.

40:47.112 --> 40:51.731
He's pretty much, like,
the only real father she ever had.

40:53.785 --> 40:55.366
Man.

40:55.871 --> 40:58.078
It's unfair.

40:58.248 --> 41:00.990
When a good thing gets destroyed...

41:01.168 --> 41:03.454
...that's the definition of unfair to me.

41:08.675 --> 41:10.211
Yeah, I know what you mean.

41:10.385 --> 41:13.343
I know exactly what you mean.

41:19.561 --> 41:21.142
G US:
I don ’t fucking trust these two.

41:21.313 --> 41:24.931
But he wouldn't fuck with me,
not now with what's downstairs.

41:28.695 --> 41:30.526
[TIRES SCREECHING]

41:51.385 --> 41:54.127
I can hear you. What do you want?

41:54.304 --> 41:56.215
Uh.... It's Hoyt Fortenberry.

41:56.390 --> 41:58.506
We met last night.

41:58.767 --> 42:02.100
-|'m the--
-I know who you are.

42:06.024 --> 42:08.401
-|'m-- I'm sorry to bother you.
-No, it's okay, I--

42:10.987 --> 42:12.818
Listen, I'm gonna unlock the door...

42:12.989 --> 42:15.696
...and then go in the living room
where it's light tight.

42:16.201 --> 42:18.908
Wanna meet me there in, like, 10 seconds?

42:20.205 --> 42:21.741
Sure.

42:42.602 --> 42:44.433
[SIGHS]

42:52.738 --> 42:56.105
I really wasn't trying to bother you.
Ijust-- I thought you'd be asleep.

42:56.283 --> 42:58.740
No, I wasn't sleeping. Um....

42:59.578 --> 43:01.239
Thinking too much, I guess.

43:01.413 --> 43:04.780
Jason told me about Mr. Compton.

43:06.001 --> 43:07.662
I really am sorry, Jessica.

43:08.170 --> 43:09.785
Thank you.

43:10.297 --> 43:11.332
I brought him this.

43:12.257 --> 43:13.713
What is it?

43:13.884 --> 43:15.249
HOYT:
I went to the clinic.

43:15.719 --> 43:17.960
And I'm negative,
and I figured the last thing...

43:18.138 --> 43:21.676
...you need to worry about
is tracking down clean blood for him.

43:23.185 --> 43:24.846
Wow, that's-- That's awfully--

43:25.020 --> 43:27.432
Awfully thoughtful of you.

43:27.606 --> 43:30.723
Especially considering everything
that you've been through.

43:32.152 --> 43:35.189
I'm-- I heard about your mother.

43:36.031 --> 43:37.396
I'm really very sorry.

43:38.909 --> 43:40.445
Thank you.

43:40.619 --> 43:42.701
I forget what a small town this is.

43:42.871 --> 43:46.329
I think because I wasn't there for her
at the end, I was beating myself up.

43:46.500 --> 43:47.660
And I talked to Jason.

43:48.376 --> 43:51.459
And he told me how Close
you and Bill are.

43:51.630 --> 43:57.626
And it struck me that maybe not knowing
my mama's time was coming was a....

43:57.803 --> 43:59.168
Like a little gift.

43:59.346 --> 44:03.840
So I didn't have to sit around
thinking about the inevitable.

44:04.017 --> 44:05.928
And then I thought...

44:06.728 --> 44:10.937
...if there's anything I could do for you
to make this an easier time, then....

44:12.818 --> 44:15.275
Well, I'm not trying
to overstep any boundaries.

44:15.445 --> 44:18.152
Wait, do you, um--? Tell me, you miss her?

44:27.165 --> 44:29.121
Yes and no.

44:29.292 --> 44:32.079
It's just no matter how grown up you get...

44:32.254 --> 44:36.293
...or how well you can stand
on your own two feet...

44:36.466 --> 44:38.707
...the death of a parent...

44:40.053 --> 44:42.590
...just makes you wanna go back.

44:43.849 --> 44:48.468
Just go back
to when you were a little kid, and....

44:49.229 --> 44:52.141
And knowing that you were loved
was all you needed.

44:52.315 --> 44:53.896
Just”.

44:55.902 --> 44:57.813
Just go back, you know?

44:57.988 --> 44:59.774
Yeah.

45:01.408 --> 45:04.775
You know, Bill ain't even gone yet, but I--

45:06.121 --> 45:07.986
I think I know exactly what you mean.

45:14.254 --> 45:16.461
I should probably get going back to Brigette.

45:17.465 --> 45:19.046
The sun's setting and all.

45:21.094 --> 45:23.005
How, uh...?

45:23.179 --> 45:25.215
How long are the two of you
gonna be in town?

45:25.390 --> 45:28.348
We leave the day after tomorrow.
I gotta get back to work.

45:28.518 --> 45:31.134
Of course, right. Alaska.

45:33.815 --> 45:37.103
Well, you'll be in my thoughts.

46:10.769 --> 46:12.760
[THUDDING]

46:26.201 --> 46:29.068
You? How the fuck do you play into all this?

46:29.496 --> 46:31.908
[SARAH MUMBLING INDISTINCTLY]

46:35.502 --> 46:37.709
Oh, Sookie Stackhouse. You're a miracle.

46:37.879 --> 46:41.292
-I knew it from the first day I laid eyes on you.
-Tell me about the cure.

46:41.466 --> 46:44.128
I will, I promise you.
First you gotta get me out of here.

46:44.302 --> 46:46.338
No fucking way. Tell me what you know.

46:46.513 --> 46:49.255
What I know is that we--

46:49.432 --> 46:50.467
You and I.

46:50.642 --> 46:54.305
--have a chance to deliver peace
unto earth for all time.

46:54.479 --> 46:56.265
A return to Eden.

46:56.731 --> 47:01.350
But first, you gotta get me the fuck
out of this dungeon of hell.

47:02.237 --> 47:04.228
I knew no good could come
from you talking.

47:06.616 --> 47:09.107
No, please don't--

47:10.120 --> 47:11.951
[SARAH SOBBING]

47:16.584 --> 47:17.619
[SARAH GASPS]

47:21.131 --> 47:22.917
[ERIC YELLS]

47:25.510 --> 47:28.468
You're a very valuable young woman.

47:31.474 --> 47:32.509
[GRUNTING]

47:41.234 --> 47:45.819
Even as the cure,
you're still the fucking problem.

47:45.989 --> 47:48.651
But I'm not letting you ruin the life...

47:48.825 --> 47:52.113
...of one more person that I love.

47:57.042 --> 47:58.578
[MUFFLED GRUNTING AND SOBBING]

48:16.561 --> 48:17.721
SooHe?

48:17.896 --> 48:19.136
-There's a cure.
-What?

48:19.314 --> 48:22.681
It's a motherfucker to explain, but it's real.
Eric is completely healed.

48:22.859 --> 48:24.770
-Are you positive?
-Hundred percent.

48:24.944 --> 48:27.151
I'll explain it to you on the way to Fangtasia.

48:27.322 --> 48:30.314
We gotta get Bill so we can leave
the second the sun goes down.

48:30.492 --> 48:31.948
-Wait, Sookie.
-What?

48:32.577 --> 48:35.159
Are you telling me
that Bill is gonna survive?

48:35.789 --> 48:39.702
Yeah, that's what I'm telling you, sweetie.

48:39.876 --> 48:41.992
It's all gonna be okay.

48:48.218 --> 48:49.549
[GRUNTING]

48:54.557 --> 48:57.549
[HUMMING]

49:15.995 --> 49:17.326
SOOKI E:
Bill, wake up.

49:17.539 --> 49:18.699
[GASPS]

49:19.666 --> 49:21.452
There's a cure.

49:26.005 --> 49:27.586
GUS:
Y'all get any sleep?

49:27.757 --> 49:30.669
A couple hours. Thanks for asking.

49:30.844 --> 49:33.586
So I gotta hop on a flight to Dallas...

49:33.763 --> 49:35.424
...but I'll be back before sunrise.

49:35.598 --> 49:37.714
Well, if you need anything, just let us know.

49:40.311 --> 49:44.520
Don't do anything stupid while I'm gone,
Mr. Northman.

49:44.691 --> 49:47.353
That's what I need from you.

49:47.527 --> 49:49.483
Rig htee-o, partner.

49:51.739 --> 49:55.197
Oh, and my men will keep you company
till I'm back.

50:06.421 --> 50:07.706
PAM:
What are we doing now?

50:07.881 --> 50:09.997
We're doing something stupid, aren't we?

50:10.175 --> 50:12.632
I gotta get some of Sarah's blood to Bill.

50:12.802 --> 50:14.884
Yep, sounds pretty stupid.

50:15.054 --> 50:16.510
He's sick, Pam.

50:17.015 --> 50:19.176
He got it from Sookie,
so he's progressing fast.

50:19.350 --> 50:23.593
Of course it's happening fast. It's Sookie.
Everything She wants, she has to have now.

50:26.733 --> 50:29.395
What part of "I will come to you"
did you not understand?

50:35.325 --> 50:36.735
Oh, fuck.

50:38.077 --> 50:39.738
You look like shit.

50:40.705 --> 50:42.445
Why, thank you, Pam.

50:43.208 --> 50:44.197
[SARAH WHIMPERS]

50:44.375 --> 50:46.206
Remember me?

50:47.003 --> 50:48.914
I'm Jason's demon whore.

50:49.088 --> 50:51.670
I'm the girl that you tried
to get James to rape.

50:51.841 --> 50:53.297
-Jess. Jessica.
SARAH: Aah!

50:53.468 --> 50:54.753
Quiet, antidote.

51:05.521 --> 51:07.557
You look well.

51:07.732 --> 51:09.563
Well, I'm feeling pretty well.

51:12.237 --> 51:14.774
-You'|| tell no one about this.
-You know we won't.

51:20.536 --> 51:22.072
Go ahead.

51:28.044 --> 51:29.830
Oh, thank God.

51:34.634 --> 51:36.215
[SARAH WHIMPERS]

51:38.721 --> 51:40.336
PAM:
What the fuck are you waiting for?

51:40.515 --> 51:43.427
Drink the bitch and leave before we all die.

51:55.863 --> 51:57.569
No.

52:03.788 --> 52:05.995
I don't want the blood.
